The isMultiplicity of a property in the generators API is still not behaving as expected in every scenario. 

I tested the ditto schema generator on a vorto 0.12.4 instance and build the schema generator with the plugin api v0.12.4. The `multiple -> array` branches of the code aren't executed.

How to reproduce
---

I used this functionblock model:

```
vortolang 1.0
namespace org.eclipse.vorto
version 1.0.0
displayname "FBTest"
description "Functionblock for FBTest"

functionblock FBTest {
    status {
	    mandatory multiple foos as string
	    optional date as dateTime
	}
}
```

The resulting schema is this

```json
{
	"$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#",
	"title": "Properties validation of definition <org.eclipse.vorto:FBTest:1.0.0>",
	"type": "object",
	"properties": {
		"status": {
			"type": "object",
			"properties": {
				"foos": {
					"type": "string"
				},
				"date": {
					"type": "string"
				}
			},
			"required": ["foos"]
		}
	},
	"required" : ["status"]
}
```

I'd expect it to be:

```json
"foos": {
	"type": "array",
	"items": {
		"type": "string"
	}
},
```

